459 
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B7028EFD474FB7AA923" box="[1222,1242,1560,1583]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
</elevation>
, 361 
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B702935D47BFA84A923" box="[1308,1316,1559,1583]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">f</emphasis>
, from 100 localities. Locality information and depositories of these examined specimens is provided in Appendix 
<tableCitation id="6407EA88AC1F3B702935D456FAD2A95F" box="[1308,1394,1594,1619]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="68.[119,196,494,513]" captionText="TABLE 5. Lisŧ of localiŧies reviseđ of eacħ Sphenarium species aŊđ morpħoŧypes (Ŋumbers wiŧħiŊ pareŊŧħesis) iđeŊŧifieđ. Localiŧies iŊcluđeđ our geŊeŧic aŊalysis are đeŊoŧeđ iŊ bolđ. For localiŧy we iŊđicaŧe iŧs localiŧy Ŋumber (LN), đescripŧioŊ, Ŋumber specimeŊs (F, females and M, males) eXamiŊeđ, đeposiŧory of ŧħe eXamiŊeđ maŧerial as iŊđicaŧeđ iŊ ŧħe meŧħođs" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Table 5</tableCitation>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293ADF33AC1F3B702CEED432FE0FA85C" blockId="24.[151,1437,151,1872]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B702CEED432FE72A97B" bold="true" box="[199,466,1630,1655]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Taxonomic discussion.</emphasis>
Charpentier (1842) described this species apparently based on two females and males 
<typeStatus id="F63E6191AC1F3B702CBED4EFFF59A997" box="[151,249,1667,1691]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">syntypes</typeStatus>
from an unspecified Mexican locality. After its original description the taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName id="EE85A4B0AC1F3B7029AED4EFFE8FA9B3" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Sphenarium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B7029AED4EFFE8FA9B3" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained unchanged until 
<bibRefCitation id="4D14A2C2AC1F3B702E56D4CAFCBBA9B3" author="Boyle" box="[639,795,1702,1727]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refString="Boyle, W. K. (1974) A Revision of the Genus Sphenarium (Orthoptera: Pyrgomorphidae). McGill University, McGill, 214 pp." type="book" year="1974">Boyle (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4D14A2C2AC1F3B702F48D4C4FBA3A9B3" author="Kevan" box="[865,1027,1703,1727]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refString="Kevan, D. K. M. (1977) The American Pyrgomorphidae (Orthoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 36 (1 - 4), 3 - 28." type="journal article" year="1977">Kevan (1977)</bibRefCitation>
recognised it as a subspecies, 
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B7029AED4CBFE78A9EF" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName id="EE85A4B0AC1F3B7029AED4CBFE74A9EF" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Sphenarium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purpurascens" subSpecies="purpurascens">S. purpurascens purpurascens</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="4D14A2C2AC1F3B702E7AD4A6FCDEA9EF" box="[595,894,1738,1763]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refString="Pedraza-Lara, C., Barrientos-Lozano, L., Rocha-Sanchez, A. Y. &amp; Zaldivar-Riveron, A. (2015) Montane and coastal species diversification in the economically important Mexican grasshopper genus Sphenarium (Orthoptera: Pyrgomorphidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 84, 220 - 231." type="journal article">
Pedraza-Lara 
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B702ED8D4A0FC8BA9EF" box="[753,811,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4D14A2C2AC1F3B702F90D4A6FAA1A9EF" box="[953,1281,1738,1763]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refString="Sanabria-Urban, S., Song, H., Oyama, K., Gonzalez-Rodriguez, A., Serrano-Meneses, M. A. &amp; Cueva del Castillo, R. (2015) Body size adaptations to altitudinal climatic variation in neotropical grasshoppers of the genus Sphenarium (Orthoptera: Pyrgomorphidae). Plos ONE, 10 (12), 1 - 24." type="journal article">
Sanabria-Urbán 
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B70285AD4A0FB0EA9EF" box="[1139,1198,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed the elevation of this species at the species level considering principally its morphological distinctiveness. Based on the morphological, genetic and geographical cohesiveness of this species we also consider 
<taxonomicName id="EE85A4B0AC1F3B70285AD57FFA88A827" box="[1139,1320,1811,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Sphenarium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpurascens">
<emphasis id="1BF10321AC1F3B70285AD57FFA88A827" box="[1139,1320,1811,1835]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. purpurascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species within the genus.
</paragraph>
